A heat map illustrating the U.S. states with the highest proportion of ENTs over 60 and the current geographic COVID-19 case volume was depicted in Fig. 1
. COVID-19 case volume was accurate as of April 14th, 2020. The highest risk states for older ENTs, defined by the ratio of total confirmed COVID-19 case volume to the total number of ENT providers over 60, were New York, New Jersey, Massachusetts, and Michigan, among others (Table 2
). The highest number of confirmed COVID-19 cases per ENT over 60 years old was New York (721) and the lowest was Hawaii (28). Data for Vermont, North Dakota, South Dakota, Wyoming, and Alaska were not incorporated into the heat map as there were fewer than 10 ENT providers over 60 in each of these states, which was the AAMC's cut-off for publishing a given state's data.
